-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-09/bank-of-america-hires-jpmorgan-s-alan-todd-for-cmbs-research.html
Bank of America Corp. (BAC)  hired Alan Todd
from  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM)  to head commercial-mortgage bond
research.  Todd, 38, who will be based in New York, will report to
Chris Flanagan, the head of U.S. mortgages and structured
finance research, Bank of America said today in a statement
distributed by Business Wire.  Todd had headed U.S. commercial mortgage-backed-securities
research at JPMorgan since 2005, according to the statement. Ed
Reardon, who has been with JPMorgan since 2000, will take the
role of lead CMBS strategist, according to bank spokeswoman
Sarah Stipicevic. He previously focused on non-agency mortgage-
backed securities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah Mulholland in New York at 
 smulholland3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alan Goldstein at 
 agoldstein5@bloomberg.net  